  "factionRules": [
    {
      "name": "Elemental Storm",
      "description": "It is said by some battle-brothers that their Chapter’s Wolf Scouts take the storm with them. In many cases, these tempestuous upheavals truly are supernatural, called into being by accompanying Rune Priest Skjalds. At other times, Wolf Scouts skilfully time their hunts to coincide with local atmospheric phenomena or instigate them with arcane technologies. Wolf Scouts can operate for extended periods hidden by such storms; using the cover to mask their movements and confuse the senses of their prey, their enemies feel they are fighting the very elements themselves."
    },
    {
      "name": "Tary",
      "description": "apons and stats, who are heavily m you have a group of potent ndance of plasma weaponry and y to double-shoot with them. Even 3AP to do so, your opponent will be espect the threat, preventing them lax or overly aggressive with their positioning. nt operatives in this kill team have unique rules to really make the e. The Pack Leader gives you an -roll, and the Grizzled Veteran rule gladly take on the toughest fights. The r will give some great board control aywire mine, and the Fangbearer support operative with their ng Spiritual Chirurgy rule. Priest Skjald gives you some extra with its Call the Storm action by operative to be obscured. Note that ve doesn’t have to be on Conceal for curing a double-shooting Gunner storm is a great trick. m is just five Space Marines, but it’s by a Fenrisian Wolf – a great tactical used right. This operative can’t oe with tougher operatives like the s can, but it has permanent Charge and great Attacks. It also has the ounce rule, a strategic gambit that to get an early Charge in to tie up a key rative (or operatives if it multi-charges base). This is an excellent tactic to ponent’s initiative gambit: this is when aggressively in the previous turning der to be offensive at the start of the ounce rule can hinder this entirely – nning play when you pull it off. e Wolf Scouts are an elite team with te strengths of the Adeptus Astartes. with slightly less durability they can forgiving. Therefore, they will reward t utilise their storm and the unique n their rules to elevate their operatives ing the apex predators of Kill Team."
    },
